out  143 411 and finished April with  163 279  a gain of 13 9  net of fees  The large cap group began the year with  134 154 and finished April with  153 689  a gain of 14 6  net of fees  Over the same time period the S P500 Stock Index gained 10 6    Time Period  Combined Portfolios A B  S P 500 Stock Index  October 2006 April 2013 58 5  19 1  April 2012 April 2013 14 2  14 0  April 2011 April 2012 1 0  3 5  April 2010 April 2012 18 7  15 6  Considering that over these time periods the portfolios usually held 5  to 10  of its assets in cash  the investment returns have been outstanding  Since fall 2006 the Group has not been required to liquidate the portfolio each summer  In August 2013  a third group will be added  There will be a large cap  a mid cap  and a small cap portfolio  Each group will begin the academic year with  100 000 and will continue to maintain the portfolios over subsequent summers  The expansion to three groups means an additional 12 cadets will be added  bring total membership to 43 regular members and four alternates  In November 2012  ten cadets along with Cols  West and Moreschi traveled to NYC on the 10th annual investment trip  Highlights included informative meetings at Bloomberg  financial data and software provider  JP Morgan  trading  and TM Capital  investment banking  Several NYC alumni  and CIG alums  hosted the cadets to dinner at O Lunney s  Spring 2013 Newsletter Field Test  Faculty Research  New Faculty  Cadet Investment Group  Cadet Internships  Honor Societies  Cadet Awards  Memo of Understanding  Alumni Survey VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility t